Please install folowing gems to run the Tweets.rb:- rest-client and json

$ruby Tweets.rb --help
Usage: opt_parser COMMAND [OPTIONS]

Commands
     Tweets: tweets #hashtag (if you try with this command then you will get the latest tweets TEXT based on your hash_tag)
     Trends: trends (if you try with this command then you will get the name and url of trends)
     Twitteri_API: api (if you try with this command then you will get the twitter api)
     Screen_name: screen_name username (if you try with this command then you will get User information in XML format)

Options
    -h, --help                       help
please run the following command:- $ruby Tweets.rb --help

Getting trends name and URL from the command Line
example: 
$ruby Tweets.rb trends
-------------------------- TWITTER TRENDS --------------------------
